    "plan_content": "Here's the complete plan for implementing the Stepper component:\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**4 file changes — 2 creates, 2 edits:**\n\n| Action | File |\n|--------|------|\n| Create | `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx` |\n| Create | `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx` |\n| Edit | `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/_registry.ts` (line 563) |\n| Edit | `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/_registry.ts` (line 2124) |\n\n---\n\n### `stepper.tsx` — Architecture\n\n**Two React contexts** (modeled after `carousel.tsx`):\n- `StepperContext` — root; holds `activeStep` + `orientation`\n- `StepperItemContext` — per-item; holds `step` + computed `\"completed\" | \"active\" | \"pending\"` state\n\n**Seven named exports** with full convention compliance (`\"use client\"`, function declarations, `data-slot`, `React.ComponentProps<\"element\">`, `cn()`):\n\n- `Stepper` → `<div data-slot=\"stepper\" data-orientation=\"...\">` wrapping a Context.Provider\n- `StepperItem` → `<div data-slot=\"stepper-item\" data-step data-state>` with its own Context.Provider\n- `StepperTrigger` → `<button>` reading step from `StepperItemContext`, shows `step + 1` by default; all state styling via `data-[state=completed]:bg-primary` etc. (no JS conditionals)\n- `StepperTitle` / `StepperDescription` → simple `<p>` wrappers\n- `StepperSeparator` → `<div>` reading both contexts; `flex-1 h-0.5` (horizontal) or `flex-1 w-0.5` (vertical); becomes `bg-primary` when `activeStep > step`\n- `StepperContent` → renders `null` when `step !== activeStep`\n\nNo npm dependencies needed (pure React + `cn()`).\n\n---\n\n### `stepper-demo.tsx` — Layout\n\nThe separator lives **inside** each non-final `StepperItem` (in the trigger row alongside the `StepperTrigger`), giving it natural `StepperItemContext` access. The item itself is `flex-col` so labels appear below. \"Next\"/\"Previous\" `Button`s navigate with disabled guards at step boundaries. The demo registers with `registryDependencies: [\"stepper\", \"button\"]`.\n\n---\n\n### Registry Insertions\n\n- **UI `_registry.ts`**: Insert `stepper` entry alphabetically between `spinner` (ends line 563) and `switch` (starts line 564)\n- **Examples `_registry.ts`**: Insert `stepper-demo` entry between `spinner-item` (ends line 2124) and `switch-demo` (starts line 2125)",
